    "However, this approach requires an enormous amount of training to achieve strong performance (Chen et al., 2023).",
    "Further, we find that self supervision can undo the benefits of instruction tuning (see Section 5.3).",
    "Alternatively, continued training of models with instructions from specialized domains significantly improves performance (Scialom et al., 2022; Shi and Lipani, 2023; along with task attributes, to generate instruction tuning data.",
    "For each unannotated text, it generates an instruction that references the text and a target response.",
    "The instruction tuning data is then used to (further) fine-tune a language model, adapting it to the task in the specialized domain."
